{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RojacU5DhHkJMDkgTqxkPU","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"current Node.js LTS major version 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Node.js — Node.js Releases\",\"url\":\"https://nodejs.org/en/about/previous-releases\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js | endoflife.date\",\"url\":\"https://endoflife.date/nodejs\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js — Node.js 26.0.0 (Current)\",\"url\":\"https://nodejs.org/en/blog/release/v26.0.0\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js 26 Released: What's New | InMotion Hosting\",\"url\":\"https://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/news/nodejs-v26-released/\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js — Evolving the Node.js Release Schedule\",\"url\":\"https://nodejs.org/en/blog/announcements/evolving-the-nodejs-release-schedule\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js Moves to One Major Release Per Year, Starting with Node 27 - InfoQ\",\"url\":\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/06/nodejs-release-changes/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - nodejs/Release: Node.js Release Working Group · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/nodejs/release\"},{\"title\":\"Node 22 vs Node 24 in 2026: Current LTS Upgrade Guide — PkgPulse Guides\",\"url\":\"https://www.pkgpulse.com/guides/nodejs-22-vs-nodejs-24-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Node.js v26 Is Here: What Actually Changed\",\"url\":\"https://nodesource.com/blog/nodejs-v26-is-here\"},{\"title\":\"What's new in Node.js 26\",\"url\":\"https://nodejsdesignpatterns.com/blog/whats-new-in-nodejs-26/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the current Node.js LTS major version in 2026:\n\n## Current LTS Status in 2026\n\nNode.js 24 is the current active LTS line in May 2026. Node.js 22 is still a supported maintenance LTS line, and Node.js 26 is the Current non-LTS line until October 2026.\n\n## Release Schedule Changes\n\nNode.js 26 will enter LTS in October 2026. After that, the release model is changing: Node.js will change its release schedule starting with version 27 in October 2026, moving from two major releases per year to one. All releases will become Long-Term Support (LTS), removing the distinction between odd and even versions.\n\nIn summary, as of June 2026, **Node.js 24** is the current active LTS version, with Node.js 26 becoming LTS later in October 2026.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"731d2fbe-73aa-4492-8eb0-4bf77b690f38","uuid":"16964531-2593-4540-ad08-0a698d2cd45d","timestamp":"2026-06-10T10:06:24.122Z","tool_use_result":{"query":"current Node.js LTS major version 2026","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_fixture_0001","content":[{"title":"Node.js — Node.js Releases","url":"https://nodejs.org/en/about/previous-releases"},{"title":"Node.js | endoflife.date","url":"https://endoflife.date/nodejs"},{"title":"Node.js — Node.js 26.0.0 (Current)","url":"https://nodejs.org/en/blog/release/v26.0.0"},{"title":"Node.js 26 Released: What's New | InMotion Hosting","url":"https://www.inmotionhosting.com/support/news/nodejs-v26-released/"},{"title":"Node.js — Evolving the Node.js Release Schedule","url":"https://nodejs.org/en/blog/announcements/evolving-the-nodejs-release-schedule"},{"title":"Node.js Moves to One Major Release Per Year, Starting with Node 27 - InfoQ","url":"https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/06/nodejs-release-changes/"},{"title":"GitHub - nodejs/Release: Node.js Release Working Group · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/nodejs/release"},{"title":"Node 22 vs Node 24 in 2026: Current LTS Upgrade Guide — PkgPulse Guides","url":"https://www.pkgpulse.com/guides/nodejs-22-vs-nodejs-24-2026"},{"title":"Node.js v26 Is Here: What Actually Changed","url":"https://nodesource.com/blog/nodejs-v26-is-here"},{"title":"What's new in Node.js 26","url":"https://nodejsdesignpatterns.com/blog/whats-new-in-nodejs-26/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about the current Node.js LTS major version in 2026:\n\n## Current LTS Status in 2026\n\nNode.js 24 is the current active LTS line in May 2026. Node.js 22 is still a supported maintenance LTS line, and Node.js 26 is the Current non-LTS line until October 2026.\n\n## Release Schedule Changes\n\nNode.js 26 will enter LTS in October 2026. After that, the release model is changing: Node.js will change its release schedule starting with version 27 in October 2026, moving from two major releases per year to one. All releases will become Long-Term Support (LTS), removing the distinction between odd and even versions.\n\nIn summary, as of June 2026, **Node.js 24** is the current active LTS version, with Node.js 26 becoming LTS later in October 2026."],"durationSeconds":4.939917875000001,"searchCount":1}}
